	<descriptions>
		<description descriptionType="Abstract">18O and 2H Isotopic analyses of water from main basin of Lake Kivu (Rwanda), Kabuno Bay (Democratic Republic of the Congo), inflowing river, rain, and hydrothermal hot spring. The purpose is to identify the sources of deep inflow into the lake and the lake mixing dynamics.</description>
		<description descriptionType="Other">Related publications: Katsev S., A.A. Aaberg, S.A. Crowe, R.E. Hecky, Recent warming of Lake Kivu, PLOS ONE, submitted (2014).</description>
	</descriptions>
